<div class="row justify-content-center">
  <div class="col-lg-8">
    <h1 class="mb-4">Cookie Policy</h1>
    <p class="text-muted">Last updated: <%= Date.current.strftime("%B %d, %Y") %></p>

    <div class="card mb-4">
      <div class="card-body">
        <h2 class="h4">What Are Cookies</h2>
        <p>
          Cookies are small text files that are placed on your computer or mobile device when you visit our website. 
          They are widely used to make websites work more efficiently and provide a better user experience.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="card mb-4">
      <div class="card-body">
        <h2 class="h4">How We Use Cookies</h2>
        <p>BioGrammatics uses cookies to:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Keep you signed in to your account</li>
          <li>Remember your preferences and settings</li>
          <li>Understand how you use our website (with your consent)</li>
          <li>Improve our services based on usage patterns</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="card mb-4">
      <div class="card-body">
        <h2 class="h4">Types of Cookies We Use</h2>
        
        <h5 class="mt-4">Essential Cookies <span class="badge bg-primary">Always Active</span></h5>
        <p>These cookies are necessary for the website to function properly. They enable core functionality such as:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>session_id:</strong> Maintains your login session</li>
          <li><strong>cookie_consent:</strong> Remembers your cookie preferences</li>
          <li><strong>csrf_token:</strong> Security token to prevent cross-site request forgery</li>
        </ul>

        <h5 class="mt-4">Analytics Cookies <span class="badge bg-secondary">Optional</span></h5>
        <p>When enabled, these cookies help us understand how visitors interact with our website:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Google Analytics (_ga, _gid):</strong> Tracks page views and user behavior (if implemented)</li>
          <li>All data is anonymized and aggregated</li>
        </ul>

        <h5 class="mt-4">Marketing Cookies <span class="badge bg-secondary">Optional</span></h5>
        <p>When enabled, these cookies may be used to:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Show relevant advertisements on other websites</li>
          <li>Measure the effectiveness of our marketing campaigns</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="card mb-4">
      <div class="card-body">
        <h2 class="h4">Your Cookie Choices</h2>
        <p>You have the right to:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Accept or Reject:</strong> Choose which types of cookies you want to accept</li>
          <li><strong>Change Preferences:</strong> Update your cookie settings at any time via the "Cookie Settings" link in the footer</li>
          <li><strong>Browser Settings:</strong> Control cookies through your browser settings</li>
        </ul>
        
        <div class="alert alert-warning mt-3">
          <i class="bi bi-exclamation-triangle me-2"></i>
          <strong>Note:</strong> Disabling essential cookies may prevent you from using certain features of our website, 
          such as signing in to your account or making purchases.
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="card mb-4">
      <div class="card-body">
        <h2 class="h4">Third-Party Cookies</h2>
        <p>
          We may use services from third parties that set their own cookies. These are governed by the privacy policies 
          of those third parties:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Bootstrap CDN:</strong> For loading CSS and JavaScript frameworks</li>
          <li><strong>Google Analytics:</strong> For website analytics (only with your consent)</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="card mb-4">
      <div class="card-body">
        <h2 class="h4">How to Control Cookies</h2>
        <p>You can control cookies through:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Our Cookie Settings:</strong> Click "Cookie Settings" in the footer</li>
          <li><strong>Browser Settings:</strong> Most browsers allow you to refuse or delete cookies</li>
          <li><strong>Private Browsing:</strong> Use incognito or private browsing mode</li>
        </ul>
        
        <h5 class="mt-4">Browser-Specific Instructions:</h5>
        <ul>
          <li><a href="https://support.google.com/chrome/answer/95647" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Chrome</a></li>
          <li><a href="https://support.mozilla.org/en-US/kb/cookies-information-websites-store-on-your-computer" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Firefox</a></li>
          <li><a href="https://support.apple.com/guide/safari/manage-cookies-and-website-data-sfri11471/mac" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Safari</a></li>
          <li><a href="https://support.microsoft.com/en-us/help/17442/windows-internet-explorer-delete-manage-cookies" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Internet Explorer/Edge</a></li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="card mb-4">
      <div class="card-body">
        <h2 class="h4">Changes to This Policy</h2>
        <p>
          We may update this Cookie Policy from time to time. We will notify you of any changes by updating the 
          "Last updated" date at the top of this policy.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="card mb-4">
      <div class="card-body">
        <h2 class="h4">Contact Us</h2>
        <p>If you have questions about our use of cookies, please contact us at:</p>
        <address>
          <strong>BioGrammatics</strong><br>
          Email: privacy@biogrammatics.com<br>
          <%= link_to "Privacy Policy", privacy_path %><br>
        </address>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="text-center mt-4">
      <button type="button" class="btn btn-primary" onclick="manageCookies()">
        <i class="bi bi-gear me-2"></i>Manage Cookie Settings
      </button>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>